President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Martin Gruenberg as Chair and Member of the Board of Directors of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC). Gruenberg is currently the Acting Chairman and Member of the Board of Directors of the FDIC, having joined in August 2005. He has held various positions within the FDIC, including Vice Chairman, Chairman, and Acting Chairman. Prior to his role at the FDIC, Gruenberg worked on the staff of the U.S. Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs. He holds a J.D. from Case Western Reserve Law School and an A.B. from Princeton University.